                                     TITO
                                     ----
       ((INTRODUCTION))

            TITO was developed to provide an improved utility for magnetic tape
       work on the TYMCOM-X systems.  TITO can read TEX format tapes but it may
       have trouble reading the older 'FAILSA' format (FAILSAFE  is  documented
       elsewhere).    TITO   cannot  perform  any  'magnetic  tape  conversion'
       functions nor handle tapes from anywhere else but the TYMCOM-X systems.

            In addition, TITO allows the  operator  to  verify  that  checksums
       agree  -  a certain method of assuring that none of the file has changed
       during the transfer to or from tape.  TITO  allows  storing  of  a  file
       across the physical tape boundary and has the ability to continue a tape
       job on a different tape device than the one initially  assigned  to  the
       job.   It  allows  more  selectivity  in determining which files will be
       operated upon for selected commands, and how much detail to type out  on
       the  operator's  terminal  for tape to disk and disk to tape procedures.
       TITO is better able to recover from certain common  tape  format  errors
       than   earlier   tape  utilities.   Finally,  the  program  will  accept
       previously created indirect or command file  inputs.   Use  of  indirect
       files,  carefully  created,  is  a technique that can save much time for
       experienced operators.






























