                         INITIALIZATION FOR STORE JOBS
                         -----------------------------

            With the  exception  of  the  CUT  AFTER  command,  which  requires
       confirmation,  and  is not recommended except as a 'last resort', a tape
       may not be written on until it has  been  initialized.   There  are  two
       methods  provided  for  initializing  tape.   These are (a) the NEW TAPE
       command;  (b) the APPEND command.

          The NEW TAPE command rewinds the tape to load point so that the  next
          STORE command will begin with SAVESET NO.  1, FILE NUMBER 1.

          The APPEND command spaces the tape out to the logical  end  of  tape.
          Unless  TITO is certain that the tape is positioned at logical end of
          tape, a rewind is automatically issued first.

                     TRANSLATION OF USERNAMES FOR RESTORES
                     -------------------------------------

               Frequently it is necessary to restore files to a  user  on  disc
          which  differs  from the user on tape.  The GET command does this for
          one user (restoring  files  to  username  running  TITO),  but  often
          several  usernames  are  involved  and  the  restore  destination  is
          different from the username running  TITO.   For  this  function  the
          TRANSLATION  command is used.  It sets up a table of destination user
          names and prior to restoring, TITO substitutes the  username  in  the
          translation table for the username on tape.


                                          NOTE

              All usernames not referenced by this translation  table  will
              be skipped during subsequent TITO commands.  Also, TEX format
              tapes which do not use usernames will also be skipped.  It is
              recommended  you  set  MODE  RESTORE  FILES (described later)
              whenever you TRANSLATE.



          The translation table may be set up by using  the  TRANSLATE  command
          and  then entering the disc username and tape username seperated by a
          back arrow or underscore character.

          Alternately, disk/tape username pairs may be included as part of  the
          RESTORE  or  GET command strings.  For example, the following command
          is presented:  

          "*"RES (MARTINEZ)(TRAINING)TAPE.DOC.

       The translation table is automatically cleared after the  command  using
       it has executed.


