                              THE DEVICE COMMAND
                              ------------------

            The DEVICE command can be used to change the tape drives  or  drive
       density setting without quiting from TITO.  It has the form

                 DEVICE DEVNAME DENSITY(CR)

       where DEVNAME and DENSITY are optional.   If  DEVNAME  is  missing,  the
       current  device is implied;  if DEVNAME is present, TITO attempts to use
       this device.  If DENSITY is missing, the command merely prints all known
       characteristics  of the device (or interrogates the operator for them if
       the device is a new one unknown to TITO).  If DENSITY is  present,  then
       TITO  will attempt to set that density and ask for it to be reentered if
       the device is incapable of this density setting.

                            MISCELLANEOUS COMMANDS
                            ----------------------

            The WHERE command prints the last tape position number  read.   The
       tape  will  probably  be  positioned  a  few  records past this position
       number.  TITO prints "position unknown" if the current  position  number
       is  meaningless.   Another way to get your current position number is to
       type 'W(cr)' when prompted for tape position range during the RESTORE or
       GET  commands.   Be  advised  this command is somewhat untrustworthy and
       should not be used for determining tape position for CUT AFTER input.

            The COF command Changes  the  Output  File  from  terminal  to  the
       specified  device  until  changed by another COF command.  These devices
       are valid objects for the COF command:  PRinter, TERminal, TELetype, and
       a  filename  in  the directory of the operator running the TITO program.
       Use a form of 'COF FILENA.ME' if it is necessary  to  obtain  an  online
       copy  of  a tape directory or if the line printer is unavailable at that
       time.




















