       III.  Questions Asked in Dialog Mode

       A set of questions is asked the user for the  input  and  output  files.
       The first two questions are always asked.  Depending upon the answers to
       those questions and whether  the  file  is  for  input  or  output,  the
       remaining  questions which apply will be asked.  Changes to the numbered
       questions, asked during the dialog or not, may be  made  as  noted  when
       MAGCON prompts for corrections following the dialog, or before a repeat.

       1.  FILE:

       Enter a file name which may take one of the following general forms.

                        DEVICE:FILE.EXTENSION(username)

                                      or

                           DEVICE:(username)FILE.EXT

       The complete file specification is optional and  will  take  on  default
       values  if  any  part  of  it  is omitted.  For example, the device will
       default to DSK:  and the user name to the current disk area.  The  input
       and  output  file names will be created as follows.  The file names will
       have the form FILXXX where XXX is a three-digit  number,  and  the  file
       extensions  will  have the form XXX where is XXX is the same three-digit
       number.  Numbering starts at 001 when MAGCON is run, and the values  are
       incremented as needed to get unique file names.

       If the output device is a magnetic tape, and the drive is  write-locked,
       MAGCON  allows  the  user  to  remount  the tape correctly and continue.
       MAGCON will type:

               FILE "file spec." STRUCTURE IS WRITE-LOCKED.
               REMOUNT TAPE IF YOU WISH TO CONTINUE
               CONTINUE?

       A "YES" answer tells MAGCON to  continue.   A  "NO"  answer  causes  the
       program to restart the output dialog.















