                                  MAGCON BUGS

       When you are converting from disk to tape you can use *.*  to  refer  to
       all  files  in  a  given  directory.   However, to store all the files a
       second time (i.e., REPEAT SPECS?), only the first file in the  directory
       will be stored on tape.  To get around this, answer YES to the question:
       "CHANGE INPUT SPECS?" AND "CHANGE OUTPUT SPECS?" What  you  "change"  is
       merely to type in *.* again.

       MAGCON won't write a logical end of tape mark;  this  is  not  really  a
       problem, but it means that it is impossible to APPEND to a MAGCON tape.

       The LABELS option does not work.  If you use it, you'll get  garbage  on
       the tape instead of labels.








































